Introduction

Wang Yibo is an award-winning Chinese actor, singer, dancer, TV host, and professional motorcycle racer under Yuehua Entertainment. Born on August 5, 1997, in Luoyang, Henan, China, he rose to fame as a member of the South Korean-Chinese boy band UNIQ, debuting in 2014 with their single "Falling in Love." As UNIQ's maknae, main dancer, and main rapper, Wang demonstrated his multilingual talents, becoming fluent in Chinese and Korean after completing high school in South Korea.

In 2016, Wang made his acting debut in the film MBA Partners and began hosting the variety show Day Day Up, which he continues to co-host. His breakout role came in 2019 with the drama The Untamed, propelling him to international fame. That year, he entered Forbes China's Top 100 Celebrity List at #71 and was named to their 30 Under 30 Asia list for his significant contributions to entertainment and dance.

Wang's prowess extends beyond entertainment to motorsports. Competing as part of the Yamaha China Racing Team in 2019, he won first place in his division. As a solo artist, his 2019 single "No Sense" shattered records, becoming the fastest-selling digital single on NetEase Music with over 10 million yuan in sales within hours. His songwriting debut further showcased his versatility and creative talent.

Recognized as a global cultural ambassador, Wang was appointed the Promotional Ambassador for the Luoyang Museum in 2022. In 2023, he won Best Actor at the 20th China Movie Channel Media Awards for his performances in Hidden Blade and Born to Fly. Wang continues to excel across multiple fields, blending passion and discipline to solidify his reputation as one of China's most influential stars.
